        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1966-07-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1966-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="136"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <head>136. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1" type="from"
                        >Johnson</persName> to Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1"
                        type="to">McNamara</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d136fn1">Source: Washington National Records
                        Center, <gloss target="#t_OSD1">OSD</gloss> Files: <gloss target="#t_FRC1"
                            >FRC</gloss> 330 70 A 4662, A–400.23 1966. Top Secret; Restricted
                        Data.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1966-07-12">July 12, 1966</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1968 Nuclear Weapons Stockpile</item>
                </list>
                <p>I approve the proposed Nuclear Weapons Stockpile for the end of <gloss
                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1968 submitted to me by the Department of Defense
                    and the Atomic Energy Commission on June 6, 1966.<note n="2" xml:id="d136fn2"
                        >See <ref target="#d133fn3">footnote 3, Document 133</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Accordingly, I approve a total of [<hi rend="italic">number not
                    declassified</hi>] complete nuclear weapons ([<hi rend="italic">number not
                        declassified</hi>] nuclear warhead elements) as the stockpile composition
                    for the end of <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1968. I also approve a total of
                        [<hi rend="italic">number not declassified</hi>] complete nuclear weapons
                        ([<hi rend="italic">number not declassified</hi>] nuclear warhead elements)
                    as the adjusted stockpile composition for the end of <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                        >FY</gloss> 1967. This will mean a planned production by the Atomic Energy
                    Commission of [<hi rend="italic">number not declassified</hi>] nuclear warhead
                    elements and a planned retirement of [<hi rend="italic">number not
                        declassified</hi>] nuclear warhead elements during <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                        >FY</gloss> 1968, resulting in a net reduction of [<hi rend="italic">number
                        not declassified</hi>] nuclear warhead elements during <gloss
                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1968 under the adjusted <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                        >FY</gloss> 1967 stockpile.</p>
                <pb facs="0441" n="415" xml:id="pg_415"/>
                <p>I have directed the Atomic Energy Commission to produce and retire those
                    quantities of atomic weapons and atomic weapons parts necessary to achieve and
                    maintain the approved <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1968 stockpile. I have
                    also directed the production of the additional weapons required for quality
                    assurance and reliability testing.</p>
                <p>I authorize you, in coordination with the Atomic Energy Commission, to make such
                    changes in the total stockpile not to exceed ±10% of the specifically stated
                    numbers of nuclear warhead elements to be produced and retired in <gloss
                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1967 and <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1968,
                    as may be necessary to adjust production schedules to meet <gloss
                        target="#t_AEC1">AEC</gloss> material availabilities or production
                    capability. I further authorize you to make minor changes (±10%) in strategic,
                    tactical, air defense or anti-submarine warfare warhead totals that may be
                    required because of adjusted delivery assets or changes in military
                    requirements. Any changes indicative of a major shift in defense policy or
                        <gloss target="#t_AEC1">AEC</gloss> production capability will be submitted
                    for my approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Lyndon B. Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
